    All Classes and Interfaces

    Class
    Description
    AbandonedShipCard
    Represents an "Abandoned Ship" adventure card in the game.

    Abstract class representing the state of an AbandonedShipCard.

    First state of the AbandonedShipCard effect logic.
    AbandonedShipState_2
    Second state of the AbandonedShipCard effect logic.

    Represents the "Abandoned Station" adventure card in the game.

    Abstract class representing the state of an Abandoned Station card in the game.

    Represents the first state of an Abandoned Station card in the game.
    AbandonedStationState_2
    Represents the second state of an Abandoned Station card in the game.
    AbandonGameCommand
    Represents a command to allow a player to abandon the game.

    AbstractCommand provides a base implementation for commands in the game.

    The AcceptCreditsCommand class implements a specific command for accepting credits during the game's card phase.
    ActivateDoubleCannonCommand
    ActivateDoubleCannonCommand is a command object that allows a player to activate a double cannon on their shipboard.
    ActivateDoubleEngineCommand
    Represents a concrete command that activates a double-engine component on the player's shipboard.
    ActivateShieldCommand
    The ActivateShieldCommand class represents a specific command in the game that allows a player to activate a shield generator on their shipboard during the appropriate game phase.
    AdventureCard
    Represents an abstract Adventure Card in the game.
    AdventureCardViewGUI
    Methods used to show the cards in the TUI the simple show method displays the info of the card as it is the InGame version displays the information necessary for the player to play the card
    AdventureCardViewTUI
    Methods used to show the cards in the TUI the simple show method displays the info of the card as it is the InGame version displays the information necessary for the player to play the card
    AlienAddon
    AlienAddon represents a specific type of component tile that includes additional functionality for alien presence and specific coloring.
    Bank
    The Bank class represents a repository that manages different types of GoodBlocks available in a game.
    BatteryComponent
    Represents a specialized component tile in the form of a battery compartment.
    BuildingPhase
    Represents the building phase of the game.
    BuildingShipController
    The BuildingShipController class is responsible for managing the logic and UI interactions during the ship-building phase of the game.
    Cabin
    Represents an abstract cabin component tile used in the game.
    Cannon
    The Cannon class represents a specific type of ComponentTile that includes cannon functionality.
    CardPhase
    Represents the "Card Phase" of the game, which is a specific type of GamePhase.
    CardPhaseController
    Controls the logic and rendering operations during a specific card-based phase of the Galaxy Trucker application.
    CardPile
    Represents a collection or pile of AdventureCards within the game system.
    ChooseShipWreckCommand
    ChooseShipWreckCommand represents a specific command that allows a player to interact with shipwreck components during certain game phases.
    ClientModel
    The ClientModel class is responsible for maintaining the state of the game client, including player-related data, game phase, and game components.
    ClientModelObserver
    The ClientModelObserver interface is designed to observe the state changes in a client-side game model and to update the view or perform actions based on the changes in the game state.
    CombatZoneCard
    Represents a Combat Zone card in the game, which is a type of Adventure Card that handles combat encounters.
    CombatZoneCard2
    Represents a Combat Zone Card in the game, extending the AdventureCard class.

    CombatZoneState_1
    Represents the first state in the combat zone sequence of the game.
    CombatZoneState_10
    Represents the state of a Combat Zone card at a specific point, identified as "CombatZoneState_10".
    CombatZoneState_3
    Represents the third state in the Combat Zone card's state machine.
    CombatZoneState_5
    Represents the fifth state in a sequence of combat zone states during the game.
    CombatZoneState_6
    Represents the state CombatZoneState_6 in the CombatZoneState context.
    CombatZoneState_7
    Represents the seventh state in the Combat Zone state machine.
    CombatZoneState_8
    Represents the state "CombatZoneState_8" during a combat encounter in the game.
    CombatZoneState_9
    Represents the ninth state in the combat zone sequence during gameplay.

    DestroyTileCommand

    DiscardComponentTileCommand
    Represents a command that discards the component tile currently held by a player.
    DisconnectCommand
    DisconnectCommand is responsible for disconnecting a client from the virtual server.

    EndPhase
    Represents the final stage of a game in which the game logic concludes and prepares for any cleanup or transition to a new game session.
    Engine
    Represents a specific type of component tile called Engine, which can rotate and have an activated engine on one or more sides.
    EnhancedClientView
    This interface defines the contract for a user interface component responsible for providing an enhanced view for the client in a game.
    EnterGodModeCommand
    The EnterGodModeCommand class extends the AbstractCommand abstract class and represents a command that allows a player to activate "God Mode" in the game.
    EpidemicCard
    The EpidemicCard class represents a specific type of AdventureCard that initiates an epidemic event in the game.
    FinishBuildingCommand
    The FinishBuildingCommand class represents a command issued by a player to indicate that they have completed their shipboard construction during the BUILDING or CORRECTINGSHIP phases of the game.
    Flightboard
    The Flightboard class represents a base abstraction for the game flightboard that tracks the positions of rockets and their ordered placement during the game.
    FlipHourglassCommand
    The FlipHourglassCommand class represents a command to flip the hourglass in the game.
    FXMLController
    The FXMLController class serves as an abstract base class for creating controllers in the Galaxy Trucker application that interact with the JavaFX FXML framework.
    GalaxyBackground
    Represents an animated galaxy background consisting of twinkling stars, displayed on a custom canvas.
    GalaxyStarsEffect
    Represents an animated effect of twinkling stars rendered on a transparent canvas.
    GalaxyTruckerClient
    The GalaxyTruckerClient class serves as the main entry point for the Galaxy Trucker client application.
    GalaxyTruckerGUI
    The GalaxyTruckerGUI class serves as the main graphical user interface for the Galaxy Trucker game.
    Game
    The Game class represents the core structure and functionalities of the game.
    GameController
    The GameController class is responsible for managing and controlling the flow of the game.
    GameController.GameState
    Represents the possible states of the game.
    GameInitializer
    The GameInitializer class is responsible for initializing and setting up the necessary components and cards for a game.
    GamePhase
    Represents an abstract phase in the lifecycle of the game.
    GameSaver
     
    GameType
    The GameType enumeration represents the types of games available in the application.
    GetBlockCommand
    The GetBlockCommand class represents a specific command in the game allowing the current player to retrieve a GoodBlock from the active card and place it onto a specified position in their shipboard.
    GoodBlock
    The GoodBlock enum represents different types of blocks used within the game system.
    HeartbeatManager
    The HeartbeatManager is responsible for managing and monitoring client heartbeats to detect timeouts and handle client disconnects.
    HeartbeatManager.HeartbeatDisconnectHandler
    The HeartbeatDisconnectHandler interface defines a contract for handling disconnection events in a system that monitors client activity through heartbeat signals.
    Hourglass
    The Hourglass class represents a countdown timer that decrements every second and allows actions to be executed upon completion using a callback method.
    InputCommand
    Represents a command input structure used to manage various game actions.
    LandOnAbandonedStationCommand
    The LandOnAbandonedStationCommand class represents the command executed when a player decides to land on an Abandoned Station during the relevant game phase.
    LandOnPlanetCommand
    The LandOnPlanetCommand class represents the command for a player to land on a planet during the "CARD" phase of the game.
    Level2FlightBoard
    Represents a Level 2 specific implementation of the Flightboard, designed with predefined starting positions and unique rocket placement logic for a more complex game configuration.
    Level2Game
    Represents a level 2 game, extending the functionality of the base Game class.
    Lobby
    The Lobby class manages a game lobby where players can join, set their ready status, and configure game settings.
    LobbyController
    The LobbyController class serves as the controller for the game lobby interface in the Galaxy Trucker application.
    LobbyView
    The LobbyView class represents the view component of a game's multiplayer lobby.
    ManageGoodBlocksCommand
    ManageGoodBlocksCommand is a command implementation that facilitates handling specific card states within the game when the player interacts with "SmugglersState_3" or "AbandonedStationState_2".
    Meteor
    Represents a meteor object in the game.
    MeteorSwarmCard
    Represents a meteor swarm card in the game, extending the functionalities of an AdventureCard.

    Represents the third state in the meteor swarm card's state management within the game.
    MoveGoodBlockCommand
    The MoveGoodBlockCommand class is responsible for handling the game command that moves a good block from one location on the shipboard to another.
    ObservableModel
    The ObservableModel serves as a core component in the observer design pattern, enabling the functionality to register, remove, and notify observers about changes in the state of the game.
    ObservableModelView
    The ObservableModelView class provides an implementation for managing a list of observers and notifying them about updates in the application state.
    ObserverModel
    ObserverModel defines an interface for observing and updating the state of various game-related components in a distributed or interactive gaming environment.
